catch with generic error rethrow - not ideal\\n   - Gifts: Good but has hardcoded 'PENDING' string (magic number)\\n   - Cart: Clean service\\n\\n**FE (React/TypeScript/RTK Query):**\\n\\n1. **API files:**\\n   - Good use of RTK Query with providesTags/invalidatesTags\\n   - Some use of `any` types (attendanceApi, okrApi, leaveApi)\\n   - Proper use of overrideExisting\\n\\n2. **AccountPage.tsx:**\\n   - 413 lines - reasonable size\\n   - Good separation of concerns with multiple forms\\n   - Clean TypeScript usage\\n   - No loading states, error handling, or prop drilling issues\\n\\n3. **EmployeePage.tsx:**\\n   - 311 lines - reasonable size\\n   - Clean patterns with hooks like usePermission, AccessControl\\n   - Good use of memoization\\n\\n4. **NikoPage.tsx:**\\n   - 779 lines - VERY LARGE, should be split into sub-components\\n   - Hardcoded emotion data in component (should be from API)\\n   - EMOTION_MAP created in render body\\n\\nNow I'm identifying the critical issues. The attendance module has massive code duplication across multiple files, the leaveRequests service is oversized at 656 lines, and there are hardcoded magic strings scattered throughout. The NikoPage component at 779 lines needs refactoring into smaller pieces. Beyond that, I'm seeing `any` types leaking across the FE API files, missing JSDoc comments in most places, and inconsistent error handling with empty catch blocks in some niko services. There's also mixed language usage between Vietnamese and English that should be standardized, and some files have unnecessary complexity that could be simplified.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"Now I have enough data to write the comprehensive code quality report. Let me create it:\\n\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n              \"id\": \"call_function_4mi0q9it66m6_1\",\n              \"name\": \"exec\",\n              \"arguments\": {\n                \"command\": \"mkdir -p /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/reviews\"\n              }\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 5824,\n            \"output\": 924,\n            \"totalTokens\": 101731,\n            \"cacheRead\": 89378,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 5605,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1775982347614,\n          \"responseId\": \"062a8a0d36758ec7975bb77b6a44b7d6\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"3f484677\",\n            \"seq\": 136\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}[... 76517 more characters truncated]"}],"details":{"count":39,"sessions":[{"key":"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7","kind":"other","channel":"webchat","origin":{"provider":"heartbeat"},"label":"Cron: 5p Progress Report","displayName":"webchat:g-agent-master-orchestrator-cron-ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7","deliveryContext":{"channel":"webchat"},"updatedAt":1776202992991,"sessionId":"66cf9c6c-73d9-4fe6-80d8-314f19cfac11","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":46529,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"running","startedAt":1776202992494,"childSessions":["agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:c2d275a5-d70a-4775-a268-fecf4708f133","agent:planner:subagent:63bb70ce-b5f3-48d0-a236-b6cf5d8d7922","agent:planner:subagent:ba49ac6d-ceff-4a9d-b3b1-7b89afdd88cc"],"systemSent":true,"abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"webchat","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/66cf9c6c-73d9-4fe6-80d8-314f19cfac11.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7 5p Progress Report — AHV Works] You are the 5-minute change-detecting reporter for the AHV Works ecosystem.\n\nCheck sessions_list. Compare current active sessions against the last known state stored in memory/heartbeat-state.json.\n\n**If nothing has changed since the last report:**\n- Stay SILENT. Send nothing. Not even HEARTBEAT_OK. Just exit quietly.\n\n**If there IS a change** (new session spawned, session died, agent failed, blocker appeared, task completed), compose a concise change report to group -5163901258:\n\nFormat:\n🟡 Orbis — 5p Update | {HH:MM} UTC {DD MMM}\n\nChanges detected:\n• [list of actual changes]\n\nPipeline: {HEALTHY if no failures / DEGRADED if failures}\n• Active sessions: N\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\n• Cron: 5p progress ✅ | Daily @ 5AM+7 ✅\n• Blockers: none / [list blockers]\n\nOnly send when something changed. Stay silent when stable.\nCurrent time: Tuesday, April 14th, 2026 - 9:42 PM (UTC) / 2026-04-14 21:42 UTC\n\nReturn your summary as plain text; it will be delivered automatically. If the task explicitly calls for messaging a specific external recipient, note who/where it should go instead of sending it yourself."}],"timestamp":1776202992493,"__openclaw":{"id":"a10f7e92","seq":1}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me check the current state of sessions and compare it against the last known state stored in memory."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ujkcomy4ys7u_1","name":"sessions_list","arguments":{"kinds":["agent"],"messageLimit":2}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ujkcomy4ys7u_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"memory/heartbeat-state.json"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":438,"output":85,"totalTokens":14467,"cacheRead":13944,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776202992689,"responseId":"062de7f1f07ac8d9a9742756972a3115","__openclaw":{"id":"5df8c3cd","seq":2}}]},{"key":"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081