 no meaningful change—the same five sessions are still running with the same statuses, and the direct message that ended was just a child session that completed normally rather than a parent cron job. There's a minor timestamp difference but nothing that warrants alerting.\n\nI'm realizing the heartbeat state file might not exist or the memory system isn't finding it, which is why the DTLX monitor session is still running. Looking at the telegram group messages more carefully, the most recent status from 21:37 shows the cron jobs and group session running, and nothing has changed since then. Since my job is specifically the DTLX 5p monitor and there are no actual changes to report, I should stay silent and exit quietly."},{"type":"text","text":"Stable. Silent."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":7176,"output":505,"totalTokens":22046,"cacheRead":13944,"cacheWrite":421,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776202910378,"responseId":"062de79fd0d744d598a796d3c90bd16f","__openclaw":{"id":"ba06f69c","seq":5}}]},{"key":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5163901258","kind":"group","channel":"telegram","origin":{"provider":"telegram","accountId":"main_bot"},"displayName":"telegram:g-ahv-qlhv-ecosystem","deliveryContext":{"channel":"telegram","to":"telegram:-5163901258","accountId":"main_bot"},"updatedAt":1776202833592,"sessionId":"8e0cb2bc-8245-4c89-bc2c-e3cca2257d0f","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":100319,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"running","startedAt":1776163408296,"endedAt":1776163783190,"runtimeMs":8014,"childSessions":["agent:senior-backend:subagent:f42cdd0e-8c76-42e7-ac2a-f1474568e0d4","agent:senior-frontend:subagent:cf1f74df-fd21-47ed-8a91-4c146aead234","agent:ui-ux-pro-max:subagent:469f1534-e128-44ea-af0d-73710c607372","agent:ui-ux-pro-max:subagent:ae038bd3-76fe-45b5-a5d7-b8797a299b2d"],"systemSent":true,"abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"telegram